06596nam a22006735i 9783955534837DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20192019gw     fo  d z      ger d  a97839555348377 a10.11129/97839555348372doi  a(DE-B1597)517823  a(OCoLC)1125192072  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 7aARC0060002bisacsh00aOur Bauhaus Heritage / Unser Bauhaus-Erbe :bWhere Do We Encounter the Myth in Everyday Life? Wo begegnen wir dem Mythos im Alltag? /chrsg. von Sandra Hofmeister. 1aMünchen : bDETAIL, c[2019] 4c©2019  a1 online resource (168 p.) :bNumerous Ills.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aDETAIL Special00tFrontmatter -- tImprint Impressum -- tContents -- t100 Years of Bauhaus: What Remains? -- tDesigning Life. Why we can learn more from the Bauhaus students than from its masters -- tThe Social Turn of Architecture. On the idealism of the Bauhaus and its relevance for architecture today -- tTribute to Thomas Maldonado. The aporetic aspect of the Bauhaus idea and the late-modern predicament -- tBauhaus Should be Our House: Technology by Design. A look at the Bauhaus Legacy in the US -- tBauhaus in Mexico. Hannes Meyer and the question of a failed utopia -- tThe Co-Op Principle by Hannes Meyer. Architecture as a collective design process -- tPidgin Bauhaus. The delirium of white walls and flat roofs -- tThe Bauhaus and its Books. Visual identity and media strategies -- tMasters and Weavers. On the role of women in the laboratory of modernism -- t"Very Fine People on Both Sides"? On the Bauhaus anniversary in the mirror of contemporary architecture and architectural historiography in Germany -- tAuthors -- tExplorations With Friederike von Rauch -- tAkademie der Kűnste -- tPicture Credits0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aA milestone Bauhaus birthday offers an excellent opportunity to take a critical look at its legacy in contemporary architecture: What ideals remain from this avant-garde movement? Are any of the Bauhaus principles or methods still relevant today? Throughout the book, 10 international authors explore the question of whether and where Bauhaus has left its mark on contemporary architectural events. Its political legacy of modernity is as much a focus in their essays as the significance of Bauhaus ideals for a commercialised and globalised construction industry. The individual contributions discuss these questions against a backdrop of different cultural perspectives brought to the project by authors from the USA, Mexico, Germany and Spain. A photo essay by the Berlin artist Friederike von Rauch, with photos of the Academy of Arts in Berlin’s Hansa Quarter, accompanies the texts. Designed by Werner Düttmann and Sabine Schumann, the Academy is one of the most impressive examples of post-war architecture.  aDer runde Bauhaus-Geburtstag gibt Anlass dazu, einen kritischen Blick auf sein Erbe in der Architektur der Gegenwart zu werfen: Was ist von den Idealen der Avantgarde übrig geblieben? Gibt es Grundsätze oder Methoden, die am Bauhaus praktiziert wurden und nach wie vor relevant sind? In diesem Buch gehen 10 internationale Autorinnen und Autoren der Frage nach, ob und wo das Bauhaus Spuren im zeitgenössischen Architekturgeschehen hinterlassen hat. Das politische Erbe der Moderne kommt in den Essays ebenso zur Sprache wie die Bedeutung von Bauhaus-Idealen für die kommerzialisierte und globalisierte Bauwirtschaft. Die einzelnen Beiträge erörtern die Fragen vor dem Hintergrund unterschiedlicher kultureller Sichtweisen, welche die Autorinnen und Autoren aus den USA, aus Mexiko, Deutschland oder Spanien einbringen. Ein Fotoessay der Berliner Künstlerin von Friederike von Rauch mit Aufnahmen der Akademie der Künste im Hansaviertel begleitet die Texte. Das Gebäude nach dem Entwurf von Werner Düttmann und Sabine Schumann zählt mit zu den beeindruckendsten Beispielen der Nachkriegsarchitektur.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aARCHITECTURE / Individual Architects & Firms / General.2bisacsh1 aBetsky, Aaron, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEfrat, Zvi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrampton, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranklin, Raquel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmeister, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofmeister, Sandra, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIbelings, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamos, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRauch, Friederike von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrobl, Hilde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrüby, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUrspung, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz978395553482040uhttps://doi.org/10.11129/978395553483740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783955534837423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783955534837.jpg  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019